<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=97877350513990></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f97877350513990><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=4&mid=97877350513990>Somewhat nifty little trick</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=4&mid=97877350513990#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=889><span id= >Ashbentiel</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>61 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sat, Jan 6th 9:33 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[2.76]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Let me start by saying that this is best done below 30th level or so and outdoors but can be done higher if careful/lucky. Get yourself a group of the following: Bard(you), AE caster times four, Cleric. <br><br>Have the cleric buff you nicely and turn on selo's. Take off and pull as many mobs as you feel safe with (I've pulled as many as 15 death beetles in unrest at 13th level, was insane) back to your group in a big hurry. When you near them start playing an ae damage song. As soon as you stop they should all start chain casting AE damage spells while staying back and the cleric should keep you alive.<br><br>The whole trick to this plan is staying alive, which becomes increasingly harder as mobs begin hitting harder, but it is just incredibly fun at lower levels to make a quarter bubble or more off of one pull due to nothing but good tactics and the right group.<br><br>Oh, as a note, to date not one mob has ever pulled off of me if I started the AE damage song at least two ticks before the casters started casting theirs.<br>&nbsp;<br>Ashbentiel<br>Bard of Tarew Marr<br>"I may make you feel but I can't make you think."  --Jethro Tull</td></tr>
