	   <tr><td colspan=2>Bards RULE!<br><br>Let's see, I can run faster than SOW, I can go invis and SEE invis, mezz, charm, lull, snare, heal, fear, find corpses, breathe underwater, see in the dark (as a human mind you), survive fine without food and water, swim forever, safe fall from great heights, dual wield, kite, wear pretty much any armor that isn't single class specific... all before level 30 and with NO MANA!<br><br>I've played most other classes and lost interest in almost all by level 10. <br><br>Bard is not the easiest class to play, but in my experience, definitely the most fun, exciting and versatile. Each level brings a new song and a new strategy.  Unfortunately, I've grouped with other bards that should have stuck to wizards or warriors... they, errr, sucked bad.  But, that is true of any class and is more a reflection of the actual person at the keyboard than the character.  Once you master the bard, you'll have plenty of friends and finding a group is no problem... not because of any one thing (although the clarity song at lvl 32 might be the exception) but because of the way bards can make themselves useful in almost any situation.<br><br>If you want to maximize your fun and are willingly to spend some extra time learning the skills of the bard, there's nothing better in my humble opinion.<br><br>Gonodar Chordmaster<br>Bard of the 27th Season<br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
